1
00:00:50,320 --> 00:00:51,240
It's eleven o'clock.

2
00:00:51,240 --> 00:00:52,119
Why hasn't it started yet?

3
00:01:07,200 --> 00:01:07,760
When will he arrive?

4
00:01:08,760 --> 00:01:09,200
He should be here soon.

5
00:01:09,200 --> 00:01:09,840
Sorry,

6
00:01:10,359 --> 00:01:11,079
there was a traffic jam on the way.

7
00:01:11,079 --> 00:01:11,959
I'm late.

8
00:01:22,000 --> 00:01:22,560
It's okay.

9
00:01:28,400 --> 00:01:29,159
Let's get started.

10
00:01:30,599 --> 00:01:31,200
Wait a minute.

11
00:01:33,480 --> 00:01:34,840
Before signing the contract,

12
00:01:35,519 --> 00:01:37,359
I have a few questions about the creation

13
00:01:37,959 --> 00:01:39,120
that I want to discuss with Mr. Xu.

14
00:01:39,120 --> 00:01:40,480
discuss it with you.

15
00:01:40,480 --> 00:01:41,159
Go ahead.

16
00:01:43,319 --> 00:01:45,760
Why did you rush to buy my novel's rights?

17
00:01:46,000 --> 00:01:47,760
What do you see in it?

18
00:01:48,480 --> 00:01:50,239
The publisher has its own considerations.

19
00:01:50,239 --> 00:01:51,599
What about you?

20
00:01:58,239 --> 00:01:58,799
I see.

21
00:02:00,200 --> 00:02:03,640
You still think my novel is trash.

22
00:02:04,599 --> 00:02:05,680
You said

23
00:02:05,760 --> 00:02:07,879
an author's job is to sell dreams.

24
00:02:08,120 --> 00:02:10,479
You don't want the publisher to become a dump.

25
00:02:11,800 --> 00:02:12,840
Then why didn't you stop

26
00:02:13,680 --> 00:02:15,639
the publisher from buying my rights?

27
00:02:18,840 --> 00:02:20,080
It seems that you

28
00:02:20,719 --> 00:02:22,240
are also a hypocrite.

29
00:02:22,639 --> 00:02:23,199
Mr. Li,

30
00:02:23,680 --> 00:02:24,639
don't waste time.

31
00:02:25,599 --> 00:02:26,639
You should cherish this opportunity.

32
00:02:26,639 --> 00:02:28,120
But I haven't finished my questions yet.

33
00:02:29,560 --> 00:02:30,840
I heard that you finally

34
00:02:31,280 --> 00:02:33,719
filled in the ending of Galaxy Chronicle.

35
00:02:34,639 --> 00:02:35,800
So you gave up writing

36
00:02:36,639 --> 00:02:38,639
because you couldn't write it,

37
00:02:39,639 --> 00:02:41,719
or you had a conflict with your brother Xu Mengxi,

38
00:02:41,719 --> 00:02:43,360
so he wouldn't help you anymore?

39
00:02:44,520 --> 00:02:45,120
What's this?

40
00:02:45,120 --> 00:02:46,240
What's this?

41
00:02:46,919 --> 00:02:47,800
Take a picture.

42
00:02:48,639 --> 00:02:49,120
Alright, alright.

43
00:02:50,080 --> 00:02:52,080
Mr. Li, we can sign the contract now.

44
00:02:56,159 --> 00:02:57,039
I need to think carefully

45
00:02:57,319 --> 00:02:58,360
about this collaboration.

46
00:02:59,960 --> 00:03:01,280
Mr. Xu is very capable,

47
00:03:01,879 --> 00:03:03,800
but I can't agree with his character.

48
00:03:06,479 --> 00:03:07,080
Wait.

49
00:03:10,080 --> 00:03:12,479
I've been to the steakhouse you went to with Yan Ying.

50
00:03:13,000 --> 00:03:14,439
The medium-rare steak was really average.

51
00:03:17,800 --> 00:03:18,520
And he even hit her.

52
00:03:18,520 --> 00:03:19,840
Take a picture of this.

53
00:03:19,840 --> 00:03:20,240
Big news.

54
00:03:20,400 --> 00:03:21,199
You can scheme against me,

55
00:03:21,960 --> 00:03:23,479
but you will never hurt Yan Ying.

56
00:03:27,199 --> 00:03:27,879
Is that so?

57
00:03:29,240 --> 00:03:31,120
I'm looking forward to your "no".

58
00:03:41,639 --> 00:03:42,400
Dear media friends,

59
00:03:42,400 --> 00:03:43,240
stop filming.

60
00:03:43,240 --> 00:03:44,520
Today's signing ceremony is canceled.

61
00:03:44,599 --> 00:03:45,680
Don't spread rumors.

62
00:03:57,400 --> 00:03:58,319
What's wrong with your mouth?

63
00:03:59,599 --> 00:03:59,960
Nothing.

64
00:04:05,840 --> 00:04:06,680
What's wrong with your mouth?

65
00:04:07,520 --> 00:04:08,039
Nothing.

66
00:04:08,680 --> 00:04:09,840
It just hurt a little.

67
00:04:10,680 --> 00:04:11,360
Go on.

68
00:04:13,800 --> 00:04:14,800
A publisher

69
00:04:14,919 --> 00:04:16,639
wanted the copyright of Li Si's novel.

70
00:04:17,040 --> 00:04:18,319
I went to sign the contract at noon.

71
00:04:18,879 --> 00:04:19,560
And maybe

72
00:04:20,000 --> 00:04:21,040
I'm not used to it.

73
00:04:21,399 --> 00:04:22,519
I made him angry

74
00:04:22,759 --> 00:04:23,680
and got beaten.

75
00:04:29,360 --> 00:04:30,319
It's you.

76
00:04:31,160 --> 00:04:32,319
Didn't I warn you?

77
00:04:32,600 --> 00:04:33,160
Xu Chi

78
00:04:34,639 --> 00:04:36,120
is not Li Si.

79
00:04:36,120 --> 00:04:37,120
It's Xiao Chengjing.

80
00:04:38,480 --> 00:04:39,959
But if it's Xiao Chengjing,

81
00:04:40,360 --> 00:04:42,319
why did he jump out of the book?

82
00:04:43,279 --> 00:04:45,120
Because of the continuation.

83
00:04:46,000 --> 00:04:46,720
Since

84
00:04:47,079 --> 00:04:49,120
we've all known each other's identities,

85
00:04:49,720 --> 00:04:51,920
why don't we take this opportunity

86
00:04:52,040 --> 00:04:53,079
to clear up the misunderstanding?

87
00:04:54,439 --> 00:04:54,800
Okay.

88
00:04:55,079 --> 00:04:55,680
Chief Xu,

89
00:04:56,120 --> 00:04:57,519
if I've offended you,

90
00:04:57,720 --> 00:04:58,720
please forgive me.

91
00:04:59,240 --> 00:05:00,639
After all, I've just arrived here.

92
00:05:00,800 --> 00:05:01,319
I'm not used to it.

93
00:05:02,399 --> 00:05:03,279
Not used to it?

94
00:05:03,879 --> 00:05:05,199
I see you are good at

95
00:05:05,199 --> 00:05:06,920
playing different roles

96
00:05:06,920 --> 00:05:08,240
in front of different people.

97
00:05:10,000 --> 00:05:10,759
Mr. Xu,

98
00:05:11,360 --> 00:05:13,480
I really don't understand what you're talking about.

99
00:05:13,480 --> 00:05:14,079
Really?

100
00:05:14,199 --> 00:05:15,319
Alright.

101
00:05:16,240 --> 00:05:19,240
I think he's just trying to stand up for Li.

102
00:05:19,439 --> 00:05:20,759
Don't take it too seriously.

103
00:05:23,079 --> 00:05:23,720
Okay.

104
00:05:24,319 --> 00:05:25,040
I'll take your advice.

105
00:05:25,639 --> 00:05:27,480
Yan Ying, what do you want?

106
00:05:27,800 --> 00:05:28,600
Okay.

107
00:05:34,399 --> 00:05:34,879
Medium-rare.

108
00:05:35,079 --> 00:05:35,639
Me too.

109
00:05:36,480 --> 00:05:37,079
Yan Ying,

110
00:05:37,560 --> 00:05:39,240
we had medium-rare last time.

111
00:05:39,240 --> 00:05:40,480
I think it's just so-so.

112
00:05:41,000 --> 00:05:42,879
How about we try medium?

113
00:05:43,879 --> 00:05:44,319
Hmm.

114
00:05:45,680 --> 00:05:47,720
I think medium-rare is just fine.

115
00:05:50,240 --> 00:05:51,319
I'll have medium.

116
00:05:51,319 --> 00:05:51,759
Okay.

117
00:06:02,399 --> 00:06:03,240
Oh, I'm...

118
00:06:05,279 --> 00:06:05,959
What's wrong?

119
00:06:06,800 --> 00:06:08,399
I've been feeling dizzy lately.

120
00:06:08,560 --> 00:06:09,519
And I'm also listless.

121
00:06:10,319 --> 00:06:11,399
Did you have this problem

122
00:06:11,639 --> 00:06:12,839
when you first came here?

123
00:06:13,839 --> 00:06:15,360
I was also temporarily weak

124
00:06:15,639 --> 00:06:16,920
at the beginning.

125
00:06:17,800 --> 00:06:18,639
But...

126
00:06:19,600 --> 00:06:20,879
Later, because...

127
00:06:29,439 --> 00:06:30,319
So,

128
00:06:31,319 --> 00:06:32,480
do you have a way?

129
00:06:33,079 --> 00:06:34,240
How can I have a way?

130
00:06:36,800 --> 00:06:39,319
It seems that you're still angry about the incident at noon.

131
00:06:39,839 --> 00:06:40,839
But I can understand.

132
00:06:44,040 --> 00:06:44,399
Oh.

133
00:06:46,399 --> 00:06:48,279
What's wrong with you again?

134
00:06:49,240 --> 00:06:50,240
The meat is too raw.

135
00:06:50,240 --> 00:06:51,680
I'm not used to it.

136
00:06:52,199 --> 00:06:53,079
You ordered it to be medium-rare.

137
00:06:53,079 --> 00:06:53,439
Ah.

138
00:06:53,439 --> 00:06:54,439
You can eat mine.

139
00:06:54,639 --> 00:06:55,279
Ah.

140
00:06:55,800 --> 00:06:56,680
Just order another one.

141
00:06:57,240 --> 00:06:57,720
No need.

142
00:06:58,160 --> 00:06:59,040
I don't like to waste.

143
00:06:59,040 --> 00:06:59,439
This is what I eat.

144
00:06:59,920 --> 00:07:01,000
It's okay. You can eat mine.

145
00:07:01,240 --> 00:07:02,120
I'm afraid you can't get used to it.

146
00:07:03,199 --> 00:07:04,000
I'll exchange with you.

147
00:07:04,439 --> 00:07:05,199
You can eat mine.

148
00:07:09,439 --> 00:07:10,040
Then...

149
00:07:10,439 --> 00:07:11,439
Thank you, Mr. Xu.

150
00:07:20,439 --> 00:07:21,120
Mr. Xu

151
00:07:21,399 --> 00:07:22,680
It's my fault today.

152
00:07:22,920 --> 00:07:23,360
I propose a toast to you.

153
00:07:25,120 --> 00:07:26,759
I can't drink this liquor.

154
00:07:27,480 --> 00:07:29,279
So, Mr. Xu, you won't forgive me?

155
00:07:31,480 --> 00:07:33,680
After all, I was created by you.

156
00:07:34,120 --> 00:07:35,519
I don't want you to have a misunderstanding about me.

157
00:07:36,120 --> 00:07:37,000
I'll drink for him.

158
00:07:37,399 --> 00:07:38,240
He can't drink much.

159
00:07:44,639 --> 00:07:46,240
What's wrong with you?

160
00:07:46,319 --> 00:07:47,079
Nothing.

161
00:07:49,959 --> 00:07:51,759
Last time when I turned into black and white,

162
00:07:51,759 --> 00:07:53,600
you kissed me and I was fine.

163
00:07:53,920 --> 00:07:54,839
How about this time

164
00:07:56,120 --> 00:07:58,120
you kiss him and try?
